      • lookup

        Collection<KimLookupParser.AliasWrapper> lookup(ParsingFrame pfm)
        Looks up for matches given a ParsingFrame. This is used for multiple lookups for different fragments of a parsed text.
        Parameters:
        pfm - - a ParsingFrame which has already parsed a part of the text
        Returns:
        - collection of matching wrapped Aliases

      • canPhraseGrow

        boolean canPhraseGrow(ParsingFrame pfm)
        Checks if the lexeme phrase that is currently focused by the passed ParsingFrame is a valid lexeme prefix of another alias. If it is a valid prefix - then phrase can grow.
        Parameters:
        pfm - - a ParsingFrame which has already parsed a part of the text
        Returns:
        - true is there is still a chance to find a larger phrase matching the current location of the parsed text
